      • convertToInqMap

        public static Map convertToInqMap(Map in)
        Convert a java.util.Map to an Inq map. This helper function can be used to convert any Map implementation into an Inq map of the type returned by AbstractComposite.simpleMap(). Keys and values from the input map are considered to be strings, that is, their toString method will be called.
        Parameters:
        in - a Java map
        Returns:
        An Inq map

      • convertToInqMap

      • get

        public static String get(Map map,
                         String key)
        A convenience method that applies the given key as an Any, as required for retrieval from an Inq Map.

        Parameters:
        map - the map to query
        key - the key to be applied
        Returns:
        a String by calling the value's toString() method, or null if the key is not found.
